.TH "NAVIGATIONHISTORYENTRY.URL" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
NavigationHistoryEntry.url \- NavigationHistoryEntry: url property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]url\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]NavigationHistoryEntry\f[R] interface returns the absolute URL of
this history entry.
If the entry corresponds to a different Document than the current one
(like \f[CR]sameDocument\f[R] property is \f[CR]false\f[R]), and that
Document was fetched with a \f[CR]Referrer\-Policy\f[R] header set to
\f[CR]no\-referrer\f[R] or \f[CR]origin\f[R], the property returns
\f[CR]null\f[R].
If current document is not fully active, it returns an empty string.
.SH VALUE
A string representing the URL or \f[CR]null\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] current = navigation.currentEntry;
console.log(current.url);
.EE
